descript.abstract: The Open Channel feature shows the channels throughout Brevard County that conduct stormwater. This layer was created using the USGS National Hydrography Dataset as the basis for flowlines in Brevard County.The National Hydrography Dataset (NHD) is a feature-based database that interconnects and uniquely identifies the stream segments or reaches that make up the nation's surface water drainage system.When this data was incorporated into Brevard County's SWAMP database, fields were added to further help the county Stormwater program identify and analyze channels. Watershed Management began adding canal names using the "Road Name" field in the attributes. The canal names source is Public Works Road and Bridge area managers. Maps were created showing all the channels in Brevard and given to the area managers. They were tasked with identifying county maintained ditches by their common names. The data was then added to the Open Channel layer by Watershed volunteers.

dataIdInfo.idAbs:
The Open Channel feature shows the channels throughout Brevard County that conduct stormwater. This layer was created using the USGS National Hydrography Dataset as the basis for flowlines in Brevard County.The National Hydrography Dataset (NHD) is a feature-based database that interconnects and uniquely identifies the stream segments or reaches that make up the nation's surface water drainage system.

When this data was incorporated into Brevard County's SWAMP database, fields were added to further help the county Stormwater program identify and analyze channels.

Watershed Management began adding canal names using the "Road Name" field in the attributes. The canal names source is Public Works Road and Bridge area managers. Maps were created showing all the channels in Brevard and given to the area managers. They were tasked with identifying county maintained ditches by their common names. The data was then added to the Open Channel layer by Watershed volunteers.
